#. +> trunk5
#: config.yaml:0 content/_index.md:0
msgid "End of 10"
msgstr "End of 10"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:8
msgid "Use your old computer but with fresh new software."
msgstr "あなたの古いコンピューターで新しい新鮮なソフトウェアを使う。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:10
msgid ""
"Extended support for Windows 10 [ends](https://endof10.org/press/2025-10-04-"
"extended-campaign/) on October 13, 2026."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:12
msgid "Microsoft wants you to buy a new computer."
msgstr ""
"Microsoft は、あなたに新しいコンピューターを買って欲しいと思っています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:14
msgid "But what if you could make your current one fast and secure again?"
msgstr ""
"しかし、現在のものを再び高速かつ安全にすることができたらどうでしょうか？"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:18
msgid ""
"If you bought your computer after 2010, there's most likely no reason to "
"throw it out. By just installing an up-to-date Linux operating system you "
"can keep using it for years to come."
msgstr ""
"2010年以降に購入したコンピューターであれば、捨てる理由はほとんどないでしょ"
"う。最新の Linux オペレーティングシステムをインストールするだけで、今後何年も"
"使い続けることができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:22
msgid ""
"Installing an operating system may sound difficult, but you don't have to do "
"it alone. With any luck, there are people in your area ready to help!"
msgstr ""
"オペレーティングシステムのインストールは難しそうに聞こえるかもしれませんが、1"
"人でやらなくても大丈夫です。運が良ければ、あなたの地域にも助けてくれる人がい"
"ますよ！"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:28
msgid "Find someone to help&nbsp;you"
msgstr "あなたを助けてくれる人を見つける"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:32
msgid "[Install Linux yourself →](/install)"
msgstr "[自分で Linux をインストールする →](/install)"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:36
msgid ""
"Would you like to help others keep their computer alive after "
"Windows&nbsp;10?"
msgstr ""
"Windows 10 への移行後も、他の​​方のコンピューターを使い続けられるようお手伝いし"
"ませんか？"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:40
msgid "Sign up as repair collective"
msgstr "修理団体として登録する"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:48
msgid "**5 Reasons** to upgrade your old computer to Linux"
msgstr "古いコンピュータを Linux にアップグレードする**5つの理由**"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:50 content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:38
msgid ""
"**No New Hardware, No Licensing Costs**{{< br >}} A new laptop costs a lot "
"of money, but several Linux operating systems are available for free. "
"Software updates are also free, forever. You can of course show your support "
"with donations!"
msgstr ""
"**新しいハードウェアもライセンス費用も不要**{{< br >}} 新しいノートパソコンは"
"高額ですが、Linux オペレーティングシステムの中には無料で利用できるものがいく"
"つかあります。ソフトウェアアップデートも永久に無料です。もちろん、寄付でサ"
"ポートしていただくことも可能です！"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:54 content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:42
msgid ""
"**Enhanced Privacy**{{< br >}} Windows comes with lots of ads and spyware. "
"This slows down your computer, lets companies spy on you, and increases your "
"energy bills."
msgstr ""
"**強化されたプライバシー**{{< br >}} Windows には多くの広告とスパイウェアが付"
"属しています。これにより、コンピューターの動作が遅くなり、企業がユーザーをス"
"パイできるようになり、電気代も増加します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:57 content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:45
msgid ""
"**Good For The Planet**{{< br >}} Production of a computer accounts for 75+% "
"of carbon emissions over its lifecycle. Keeping a functioning device longer "
"is a hugely effective way to reduce emissions. With a Linux operating system "
"you can use your device longer."
msgstr ""
"**地球に優しい**{{< br >}} コンピューターの製造は、そのライフサイクル全体にお"
"ける二酸化炭素排出量の75%以上を占めています。デバイスを長く使い続けることは、"
"排出量を削減する非常に効果的な方法です。Linux オペレーティングシステムを使用"
"すれば、デバイスをより長く使い続けることができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:61 content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:49
msgid ""
"**Community & Professional Support**{{< br >}} There are local repair cafes "
"and independent, professional services and computer shops available for "
"providing you help. You can find support in online forums, too."
msgstr ""
"**コミュニティと専門家によるサポート**{{< br >}} 地元のリペアカフェや、独立し"
"た専門サービス、コンピューターショップなどが、あなたをサポートします。オンラ"
"インフォーラムでもサポートを利用できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:65 content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:53
msgid ""
"**Better User Control**{{< br >}} Linux grants you the four freedoms of "
"software. You are free to use, study, share, and improve the program, for as "
"long as you wish. You are in control of your device."
msgstr ""
"**より優れたユーザーコントロール**{{< br >}} Linux はソフトウェアの4つの自由"
"をあなたに与えます。あなたは望む限り、プログラムを自由に使用、研究、共有、そ"
"して改善することができます。あなたは自分のデバイスをコントロールできます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:69
msgid "Supporters"
msgstr "サポーター"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:71
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "These organizations have joined us in support of the campaign."
msgid ""
"These organizations (listed alphabetically) have joined us in support of the "
"campaign."
msgstr "これらの団体もこのキャンペーンの支援に加わりました。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:75
msgid "Convinced?"
msgstr "決意が固まりましたか？"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:77
msgid ""
"Then find your closest repair cafe or independent computer shop and enjoy "
"your brand-new, old computer!"
msgstr ""
"最寄りの修理カフェや個人経営のパソコンショップを見つけて、新品の古いコン"
"ピューターを楽しんでください！"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:82
msgid "Repair your old computer"
msgstr "あなたの古いコンピューターをアップグレードする"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:0
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Windows 10 ends in 2025. Don’t buy a new PC — revive yours with Linux. "
#| "It's fast, secure, and help is available to get you started."
msgid ""
"Extended support for Windows 10 ends in 2026. Don’t buy a new PC — revive "
"yours with Linux. It's fast, secure, and help is available to get you "
"started."
msgstr ""
"Windows 10 のサポートは2025年10月14日で終わります。しかし新しいコンピューター"
"を買う必要はありません ー Linux であなたのコンピューターを復活させましょう。"
"高速で安全、そして使い始めるためのサポートも利用できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:0
msgid "/laptop-thumbnail.png"
msgstr "/laptop-thumbnail.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:9
msgid ""
"When can I publish our repair café or independent computer shop at "
"endof10.org?"
msgstr ""
"いつになったら、修理カフェや独立系コンピューターショップを endof10.org に掲載"
"できますか？"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:11
msgid "If you offer Linux help, you can add your location right now!"
msgstr "Linux のサポートを提供している場合は、今すぐ場所を追加できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:13
msgid ""
"A description of the information we need [for places](https://invent.kde.org/"
"websites/endof10-org#places) and [for events](https://invent.kde.org/"
"websites/endof10-org#events) can be found at the Git repository's README. "
"Send the information by email to endof10 [at] lists.posteo.de. If you can, "
"help us out by providing that information in JSON format."
msgstr ""
"必要な情報[場所について](https://invent.kde.org/websites/endof10-org#places)"
"と[イベントについて](https://invent.kde.org/websites/endof10-org#events)につ"
"いては、Git リポジトリの README をご覧ください。情報を endof10 [at] "
"lists.posteo.de までメールでお送りください。可能であれば、JSON 形式で情報をご"
"提供いただければ幸いです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:20
msgid ""
"If you have the technical know-how, you can also make a [Merge Request]"
"(https://invent.kde.org/websites/endof10-org/-/tree/master/data) yourself at "
"the End Of 10 website's repository."
msgstr ""
"技術的な知識をお持ちの場合は、End Of 10 ウェブサイトのリポジトリで[マージリク"
"エスト](https://invent.kde.org/websites/endof10-org/-/tree/master/data)を自分"
"で作成することもできます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:24
msgid ""
"See the [FAQ](https://endof10.org/faq#i-like-to-help-people-install-linux-"
"but-i-am-not-a-part-of-any-group-can-i-be-listed-anyway) for why we list "
"organizations, not individuals."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:26
msgid "How can I get involved with the campaign?"
msgstr "キャンペーンに参加するにはどうすればいいですか？"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:28
msgid ""
"There are many ways to get involved! Contact us so we can coordinate your "
"efforts with ours."
msgstr ""
"参加方法はたくさんあります！ぜひご連絡ください。皆様の取り組みと私たちの取り"
"組みを連携させていきます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:30
msgid ""
"Contact repair cafes and independent computer shops [offering Linux support]"
"(https://endof10.org/faq#is-there-any-way-at-all-i-can-offer-linux-support-"
"as-an-individual) and put them in touch with us"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:31
msgid ""
"[Organize an installation event](https://endof10.org/faq#how-do-i-organize-"
"an-install-party) or [start a Repair Cafe](https://endof10.org/faq#how-do-i-"
"organize-a-repair-cafe?) and let us know about it"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:32
msgid ""
"Design materials for new users such as guides, [promotional materials]"
"(https://endof10.org/faq#do-you-have-ads-flyers-posters-jingles-etc-for-"
"advertising-the-end-of-10-campaign), etc."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:33
msgid ""
"[Distribute materials](https://endof10.org/faq#can-i-still-help-if-i-do-not-"
"have-time-to-organize-an-install-event-or-repair-cafe) in cafes, shops, "
"universities, schools in your area"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:34
msgid ""
"Boost the campaign's online presence by sharing [our social media](https://"
"endof10.org/faq#is-the-campaign-active-on-social-media) posts on your "
"preferred platforms"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:35
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Translate the website (more below), campaign materials, etc."
msgid "Translate the website (more below), promotional materials, etc."
msgstr "ウェブサイト (詳細は下記参照)、キャンペーン資料などを翻訳します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:36
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Volunteer with FOSS communities participating in the campaign (improving "
#| "documentation, software debugging, design)"
msgid ""
"Volunteer with [FOSS communities](https://endof10.org/#supporters) "
"participating in the campaign (improving documentation, software debugging, "
"design)"
msgstr ""
"キャンペーンに参加している FOSS コミュニティでボランティア活動を行う (ドキュ"
"メント、ソフトウェアのデバッグ、設計の改善)"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:38
msgid "\\<your ideas\\>"
msgstr "\\<あなたのアイデア\\>"

#. +> trunk5
#: content/contribute.md:40
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Which communication platforms does the End Of 10 campaign use?"
